organization.description:
The Government Digital Service is a team within Cabinet Office tasked with transforming government digital services.
Established in response to Martha Lane Fox’s report, ‘Directgov 2010 and beyond: revolution not evolution’, our core purpose is to ensure the Government offers world-class digital products that meet people’s needs.

http://digital.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/category/gds/
